1) Git installation and configuration

email:
priya.shanthram@r2-factory.com
username:
priya-r2

Signup for github:
windows: Download
Mac: Type git version and download

Global config:
git config --global user.name "Name"
git config --global user.email "Email"
git config --global -l


Git basic commands:
git clone(with SSH and https)
windows ssh - puttygen
mac ssh - ssh-keygen
git status
git add (staging area)
git commit -m
git push -u origin master
git pull origin master
git log
git log --abbrev-commit

Creating Branch:
git branch
git branch -a
git branch "<branch name>"
git checkout -b "<branchname>"
git branch -d "<branchname>"
git diff <branch1> <branch2>


Merging:
Fast Forward merge
raising pull request using github


Advanced:
Git workflow: Working directory --> Staging area --> local git repo --> remote gitrepo
Tracked files
git ls-files(tracked files)
Unstaged changes ex: git restore --staged <file>
discard changes in the file: git restore <file>
git log --oneline --graph --decorate
git log -- <specific file>
git log --follow -- <specific file>
git comparison
git stash
git stash list
git stash pop
git rebase
git rebase --abort

m1 --- m2 --- m3
       |
       F1 --- F2

Best practices:
after commit git pull before push
Try not to use rebase

